"title": "5941: secrecy",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5941",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Behaving in a way designed to keep intentions or feelings hidden from others. In Scripture acting or speaking in secret is often linked with wrongdoing, although not in all cases. But nothing can be kept secret from God.</p>\n<h2>Secrecy as a cover for wrongdoing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:11-Eph5:12\">EPH 5:11–5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:6\">DEU 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:15\">DEU 27:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:24\">DEU 27:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:10\">2SA 15:10</a> <em>Absalom's camp</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:9\">2KI 17:9</a> <em>high places, centres of pagan Canaanite worship</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:24-Job31:28\">JOB 31:24–31:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:8\">PSA 10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:17\">PRO 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:23\">PRO 17:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:4\">ISA 65:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:11\">ACT 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:2\">2CO 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:72\">2TH 2:72</a>PE <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:1\">2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:4\">JUD 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>Secrecy associated with Satan and the black arts</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:24\">REV 2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:11\">EXO 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:22\">EXO 7:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:7\">EXO 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:18\">EXO 8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:7\">2TH 2:7</a></p>\n<h2>Secrecy sometimes ensures safety</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:1\">JOS 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:15-Judg3:26\">JDG 3:15–3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:12\">2SA 21:12</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:20\">EST 2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:17\">JER 13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:16\">JER 38:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24\">MRK 7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:2-John7:10\">JHN 7:2–7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:38\">JHN 19:38</a></p>\n<h2>Nothing can be kept secret from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:24\">JER 23:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:7-2Sam12:12\">2SA 12:7–12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job13:10\">JOB 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:20-Ps44:21\">PSA 44:20–44:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:8\">PSA 90:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:5\">PSA 101:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:15\">PSA 139:1–139:15</a></p>\n<h2>God's truths are not made known in secret</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:19\">ISA 45:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:16\">ISA 48:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:20\">JHN 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:26\">ACT 26:26</a></p>\n<h2>Secrecy in worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:16-Matt6:18\">MAT 6:16–6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:1-Matt6:6\">MAT 6:1–6:6</a></p>\n<h2>Secrets</h2>\n<h3>Divine secrets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:29\">DEU 29:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:5-Job11:6\">JOB 11:5–11:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:3\">EZK 28:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:10-Matt13:11\">MAT 13:10–13:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:10-Mark4:11\">MRK 4:10–4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:10\">LUK 8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:9\">ISA 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:7\">1CO 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:1\">1CO 4:1</a></p>\n<h3>Human secrets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:13\">PRO 11:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:5-Judg16:17\">JDG 16:5–16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:16\">ROM 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:24-1Cor14:25\">1CO 14:24–14:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:12\">PHP 4:12</a></p>",
